LOC=/etc/group
WHY=Authentication
DES="provides the group file
/etc/group
defines both what groups exist
and what users belong to those groups.
groups is another method for controlling access
to executables, files, and directories.

There are tools for safely editing it
But occasionally SAs edit it manually.
Group  0 is root
Groups 1 through 255 are for device node modes.
Groups 256 through 511 are for daemons and services.
Groups 512 through 1023 are reserved.
Groups 1024 through 65534 are for users.
Group  65535 is for nogroup."

MAN="5 group"
